Quote:  Ratana was a prophet who, in November 1918, claimed to have witnessed the presence of God in Aotearoa/New Zealand. According to Ratana, who later became known as the Mangai, or "God's mouthpiece". Maori people stood high in the Lord's favour, and,like the ancient Israelites, had been singled out as the instrument of His will.
